'''''Kong Strikes Back!''''' is a 1984 [[Platform game|platform]] [[video game]] published by [[Ocean Software]] in [[1984 in video gaming|1984]] for the [[Amstrad CPC]], [[Commodore 64]] and [[ZX Spectrum]]. While its predecessor, ''Kong'', is a ''[[Donkey Kong (arcade game)|Donkey Kong]]'' [[Video game clone|clone]], ''Kong Strikes Back!'' is a clone of ''[[Mr. Do's Wild Ride]]'' with ''Donkey Kong''-inspired graphics.

==Gameplay==
The player must rescue a [[damsel in distress]] on a [[rollercoaster]] in a fairground, and the goal of each level is to reach the top of the level to save her from Kong, a large ape. The player must avoid rollercoaster carts and various hazards by climbing up ladders on the track, and then climbing down and continuing up the track after the hazards pass.<ref name=amstradaction />

==Development==
''Kong Strikes Back!'s '' graphics are inspired by ''[[Donkey Kong (arcade game)|Donkey Kong]]'', while its gameplay is a clone of ''[[Mr. Do's Wild Ride]]''. ''Kong Strikes Back!'' was released in the EU in mid-November 1984,<ref name=homecomputing83 /> and TV advertisements for the game aired around Christmas 1985.<ref name=tvgamer>{{cite magazine|title =News: Leading Ocean's games list for Christmas|date =November 1984 |url =https://archive.org/stream/TV_Gamer_1984-11_Boytonbrook_GB/TV_Gamer_1984-11_Boytonbrook_GB#page/n7/mode/2up |magazine =TV Gamer |publisher =Boytonbrook|page =8 }}</ref><ref name=homecomputing83>{{cite magazine|title =News: Roland's Rat Adventure |date =October 1984 |url =https://archive.org/stream/home-computing-weekly-083/Home_Computing_Weekly_083#page/n5/mode/2up |magazine =Home Computing Weekly |publisher =[[Argus Specialist Publications]]|issue =83 |page =6 }}</ref> To promote the release of ''Kong Strikes Back!'', Ocean ran a [[caption contest]] in ''Home Computing Weekly'', with the winners receiving a copy of either the Commodore 64 or the ZX Spectrum version of the game.<ref name=contest>{{cite magazine|title =Competition: Monkey Business |date =February 1985 |url =https://archive.org/stream/home-computing-weekly-099/Home_Computing_Weekly_099#page/n7/mode/2up|magazine=Home Computing Weekly |publisher =[[Argus Specialist Publications]]|issue =99 |page =8 }}</ref>

''Kong Strikes Back!'' appears on both the ZX Spectrum and Commodore 64 versions of the 1986 video game compilation ''[[Off the Hook (video game)|Off the Hook]]'', which donated all proceeds to the charity [[The Prince's Trust]] to help fight [[drug abuse]].<ref name=computergamerAD>{{cite magazine|title =Off the Hook Magazine Advertisement|date =May 1986 |url =https://archive.org/details/Computer_Gamer_Magazine_Issue_014/page/96/mode/2up |magazine =Computer Gamer |publisher =[[Argus Specialist Publications]]|issue =14 |page =97 }}</ref>

''Kong Strikes Back!'' is one of the first games with music composed by [[Martin Galway]].{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}

